# Desktop HTML Structure (@html, @desktop)

This rule helps with:

- Enforce semantic, modular containers (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`)
- Ensure your “mode zone” element has a unique class or data-attribute (e.g. `data-mode-zone`)
- Keep the mode container wrapper at a fixed dimension in your markup
- Avoid deeply nested tags—limit to 3 levels max for readability
